article.headline: Texas-Arlington 70, Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 49
article.story: ARLINGTON, Texas -- Bo Ingram scored 16 points, making 7 of 9 from the field, to lead Texas-Arlington over Texas A&M-Corpus Christi 70-49 on Wednesday night. The Mavericks (8-9, 2-2 Southland) were trailing 30-27 at halftime, but went on a 19-3 run midway through the second half to take control for good. The final score was the Mavericks' largest lead. Cameron Catlett added 13 points for Texas-Arlington while Armani Williams and LaMarcus Reed scored 11 each. Demond Watt finished with game highs of 18 points and 12 rebounds for the Islanders (6-12, 1-3). Texas A&M-Corpus Christi kept it close during the first half and even led by four points early in the second, but they finished with just 32.1 percent shooting from the field.
